Understand the page object differences

SimpleHomePage vs a SimpleProductPage

SimpleHomePage:

Handles the "browsing" experience

Responsible for:

- Navigating to the Home page
- Clicking categories
- Selecting products from the list
- Going to the cart

SimpleProductPage:

- Handles the "product interaction" experience

Responsible for:

- Getting product details
- Addding products to the cart
- Handling add-to-cart alerts

Why this matters? Specifically referring to the seperation
- Each page object has a single responsibility
- Makes code more maintable and easier to understand**********************
- Follows the principle of seperation of corcerns
- Mirrors real-world shopping behaviour